{"parse":{"title":"Nakhl Gardani","pageid":55296379,"revid":832199247,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">Nakhl Gardani</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Nakhl_Gardani_Taft_town,_Iran.jpg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Nakhl Gardani in Taft town, Iran\"><img alt=\"Nakhl Gardani in Taft town, Iran\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/Nakhl_Gardani_Taft_town%2C_Iran.jpg/220px-Nakhl_Gardani_Taft_town%2C_Iran.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/Nakhl_Gardani_Taft_town%2C_Iran.jpg/330px-Nakhl_Gardani_Taft_town%2C_Iran.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/Nakhl_Gardani_Taft_town%2C_Iran.jpg/440px-Nakhl_Gardani_Taft_town%2C_Iran.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4000\" data-file-height=\"2667\" /></a><div>Nakhl Gardani in <a href=\"/wiki/Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque\" title=\"Amir Chakhmaq mosque\">Amir Chakhmaq mosque</a> of Yazd</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Status</th><td>\nactive</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\nreligious <a href=\"/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram\" title=\"Mourning of Muharram\">mourning</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date(s)</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Ashura\" title=\"Ashura\">Ashura</a>, 10th Muharram</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Frequency</th><td>\nAnnually</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Iran\" title=\"Iran\">Iran</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Participants</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Shia_Muslims\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shia Muslims\">Shia Muslims</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Nakhl Gardani</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Persian_language\" title=\"Persian language\">Persian</a>: <span lang=\"fa\" dir=\"rtl\">\u0646\u062e\u0644 \u06af\u0631\u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc</span>&#8206;, <small>Persian pronunciation:&#160;</small><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"/wiki/Help:IPA/Persian\" title=\"Help:IPA/Persian\">[n\u00e6xl \u0261\u00e6rd\u0251\u02d0ni\u02d0]</a></span>) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Shia_Islam\" title=\"Shia Islam\">Shia</a> religious ritual carried out on the <a href=\"/wiki/Ashura\" title=\"Ashura\">day of Ashura</a> for commemorating the <a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_Karbala\" title=\"Battle of Karbala\">death</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Husayn_ibn_Ali\" title=\"Husayn ibn Ali\">Husayn ibn Ali</a>, the grandson of the Prophet <a href=\"/wiki/Mo%E1%B8%A5ammad\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mo\u1e25ammad\">Mo\u1e25ammad</a> and third <a href=\"/wiki/Shia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shia\">Shia</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Imamah_(Shia_doctrine)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Imamah (Shia doctrine)\">Imam</a>. <i>Nakhl</i> is a wooden structure used as a symbolic representation of the Imam's <a href=\"/wiki/Coffin\" title=\"Coffin\">coffin</a> and <i>Nakhl Gardani</i> is the act of carrying the Nakhl from one place to another, resembling an Imam's <a href=\"/wiki/Funeral\" title=\"Funeral\">funeral</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Iranica_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Iranica-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The ritual is carried out in cities like <a href=\"/wiki/Yazd\" title=\"Yazd\">Yazd</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-WE_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WE-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Kashan\" title=\"Kashan\">Kashan</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Kashan_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Kashan-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/wiki/Shahrud,_Iran\" title=\"Shahrud, Iran\">Shahroud</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Nakhl\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Nakhl</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Yazd&#39;s_Nakhl\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Yazd's Nakhl</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Ritual\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ritual</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Gallery\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gallery</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Nakhl\">Nakhl</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nakhl_Gardani&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Nakhl\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><i>Nakhl</i> (date palm<sup id=\"cite_ref-Brill_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Brill-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>) is a woody structure similar to a <a href=\"/wiki/Cypress\" title=\"Cypress\">cypress</a> tree in shape,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dream_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dream-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> symbolizing <a href=\"/wiki/Husayn_ibn_Ali\" title=\"Husayn ibn Ali\">Husayn ibn Ali</a>'s <a href=\"/wiki/Coffin\" title=\"Coffin\">coffin</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Iranica_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Iranica-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Dehkhoda\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dehkhoda\">Dehkhoda</a> defines <i>Nakhl</i> as \"a big, tall bier (coffin) to which are attached daggers, swords, luxurious fabrics, and mirrors.\" <i>Nakhls</i> are constructed in various sizes, from a simple ones carried by two persons, to huge structures \"supported by hundreds of men\". According to <a href=\"/wiki/Parviz_Tanavoli\" title=\"Parviz Tanavoli\">Parviz Tanavoli</a>, an <a href=\"/wiki/Iran\" title=\"Iran\">Iranian</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Sculpture\" title=\"Sculpture\">sculptor</a>, <i>Nakhl</i> is a \"freestanding\" sculpture.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Brill_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Brill-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The structure is called <i>Nakhl</i> since it's \"widely\" believed that Husayn ibn Ali's body was moved to the shade of a palm tree, after his death, or because his body was carried using a coffin made of branches of palm tree, \"the only material available in Karbala\" at that time.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Brill_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Brill-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Yazd.27s_Nakhl\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Yazd's_Nakhl\">Yazd's Nakhl</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nakhl_Gardani&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Yazd&#039;s Nakhl\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nakhl_in_Yazd.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Nakhl_in_Yazd.jpg/220px-Nakhl_in_Yazd.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Nakhl_in_Yazd.jpg/330px-Nakhl_in_Yazd.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Nakhl_in_Yazd.jpg/440px-Nakhl_in_Yazd.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3781\" data-file-height=\"2520\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nakhl_in_Yazd.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A Nakhl in <a href=\"/wiki/Yazd\" title=\"Yazd\">Yazd</a></div></div></div>\n<p>As a \"symbol of social unity for a town, village, or district,\" many <i>Nakhls</i> and their associated rituals are seen in <a href=\"/wiki/Yazd_Province\" title=\"Yazd Province\">Yazd Province</a>, located near the <a href=\"/wiki/Dasht-e_Kavir\" title=\"Dasht-e Kavir\">Kavir Desert</a>, with every village having its own <i>Nakhl</i>. <i>Nakhl</i> is often referred to as <i>Naql</i>, i.e. \"to convey carry and transfer,\" in Yazd and neighboring towns and villages.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Brill_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Brill-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Yazd is described as \"<i>Iran\u2019s museum of mourning tools</i>\" by <a href=\"/wiki/Jalal_Al-e-Ahmad\" title=\"Jalal Al-e-Ahmad\">Jalal Al-e-Ahmad</a>, and is the home to the largest <i>Nakhl,</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Dream_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dream-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> which needs to be carried by \"several hundred men\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-WE_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WE-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The 8.5 meters high structure,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dream_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dream-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> constructed in 1879, stands in <a href=\"/wiki/Amir_Chakhmaq\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Amir Chakhmaq\">Amir Chakhmaq</a> square of Yazd city and is decayed and no longer used because of the safety concerns.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Iranica_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Iranica-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ritual\">Ritual</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nakhl_Gardani&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Ritual\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_3.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/42/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_3.jpg/220px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_3.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/42/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_3.jpg/330px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_3.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/42/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_3.jpg/440px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_3.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"800\" data-file-height=\"533\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_3.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Mourners carrying the Nakhl by holding the wooden columns</div></div></div>\n<p><i>Nakh-Gardani</i> is the act of carrying <i>Nakhl</i>, sometimes by \"several strong men\", on the Day of Ashura, as if it is Imam Husyan's coffin.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Brill_5-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Brill-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The ritual, historically dating back to pre-<a href=\"/wiki/Safavids\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Safavids\">Safavids</a> (almost 450 years ago<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dream_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dream-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>), is carried out at various places in Iran.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Hamshahri_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Hamshahri-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> People carrying the <i>Nakhl</i> on their shoulders are guided by the people standing on the Nakhl.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dream_6-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dream-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The ritual is so common in Iran that in most parts of the country, either people have the <i>Nakhl</i> in their community or at least they know about it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Tileben_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Tileben-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nakhl_Gardani&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Gallery\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-packed\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 174.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 174.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 172.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_4.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_4.jpg/259px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_4.jpg\" width=\"173\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_4.jpg/388px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_4.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_4.jpg/517px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque_4.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"800\" data-file-height=\"557\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Nakhl Gardani in Amir Chakhmaq mosque, Yazd, 2017.\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 215.33333333333px\"><div style=\"width: 215.33333333333px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 213.33333333333px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Muharram.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Muharram.jpg/320px-Muharram.jpg\" width=\"214\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Muharram.jpg/480px-Muharram.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Muharram.jpg/640px-Muharram.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1920\" data-file-height=\"1080\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Nakhl Gardani in <a href=\"/wiki/Mehriz\" title=\"Mehriz\">Mehriz</a>, Yazd.\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 192.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 192.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 190.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque.jpg/286px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque.jpg\" width=\"191\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque.jpg/429px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque.jpg/572px-Nakhl_Gardani_Amir_Chakhmaq_mosque.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"800\" data-file-height=\"504\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Nakhl Gardani in Amir Chakhmaq mosque, Yazd, 2017.\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 192px\"><div style=\"width: 192px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 190px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_(66).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg/285px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg\" width=\"190\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg/428px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg/570px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_